column13: Best game I've ever played (on any system)
column14:
This is the best game I have ever played hands down. The sheer amount of activities you can engage in in this game is very overwhelming but the good kind.
GAMEPLAY: Solid. It feels very unique but not unlike many MMOs you'd see on the Web these days. You have varied kinds of attack methods, such as Ether (magic) based ones, support (healing) and basic physical attacks along with a few others. Some of these need to be prioritized based on what type of enemy your encountering. For example, you'd want to use "Purge" to get a certain type of enemy's barrier down and can actually attack it.
THE WORLD / SETTING: This game excels at making you speechless when you encounter a new area for the first time. The amount of creativity is just so unrivaled, it really is amazing. I remember many, many times going back to a certain locations (all of them ^-^) just to sit there and take in the view. Now, before I go any further, I will say that this did look a lot better on a TV screen than on the 3DS. Why? The 3DS has to compress the image and it obviously looks a little jittery. BUT- still amazing non the less. The fact that you play on two giants is quite amazing and going back to the view part, when you for instance go to Bionis Leg (yes his leg) and you move the camera toward the sky, you will see that the other titan, Mechonis is creepily looking down on you with his blood-red eyes. It's even worse at night (in game) because that's all you can see....is....his....eyes..... This happens in many locations too. 10/10!

SOUND / MUSIC: Again, unrivaled. Each area has a two different themes, one for the daytime (lively) and one for the nighttime (somber) Not to mention you visit like 30 major places in the game. That's 60 different songs! Not even counting the cut-scene songs, intro, and battle. And it's so high quality, like not cheap. Every area's track fits it to a T. One can only wonder how much money they spent on the Orchestra....Voice acting is great! I just didn't care for Fiora's VA. It's not that she didn't deliver, it's just an annoying voice (IMO). 10/10

ART / GRAPHICS: The art in this game is beautiful is I didn't say it already. The plains look very lush, the jungle looks humid, and the marsh looks, well, like a marsh. Foggy. Like I said before, I must've visited all the areas at least 4 times JUST to look/explore it's scenery. I honesty feel like they couldn't have rendered this game any more beautiful than it already is. Graphics are from a 4 year old Wii game but HEY that does not bother me one bit, you know why? Because the art makes up for it and honestly it's not bad at all to begin with. Although I won't sugar-coat it, the Wii version did look a bit...crisper than the port for obvious reasons. 10/10

THE PORT: Here it goes: It's not the best it could've been. Every time I'd fight a huge monster (one that takes up the whole screen, the frame rate and whole game would just drop very slow. So it made the "slow time events" even slower. They should've increased the CPU or whatever it's called to make this game run more smoother. I did not have too many of these "slow battles" and they weren't unbearable but still annoying none-the-less. HOWEVER. I really don't want this part to dissuade anyone from buying this fantastic game. When Amazon asked me to review this game I wasn't even going to put this but since I'm being completely honest I thought I should. I still enjoyed it regardless. Who knows? Could just be my copy. 8/10

OVERALL: Please, please do yourself a favor and buy this game. I can almost guarantee that you'll love it. Believe it or not, I just clocked in around 160 hours or so, but that probably because I tried to take on most of the game's 400+ side quest. Just the story is about 70 something hours if your doing a speed run without the New Game+.

Buy this. I did and now I 'am a very happy person :)e for Fiora's VA. column6: King's Field: The Ancient City
column13: First person RPG madness! You do not know what you are missing if you give up in 5 min.
column14: This is  currently my favorite game for the PS2. Picture Dark souls with a first person perspective, and add a masterfully written musical score, and you have Kings Field...well, kinda. There is definitely alot of similarities between the two. The world of Kings field seems to have more of a feeling of desolation and madness. Tons of weapons and armor with a huge world to explore. AND NO LOADING SCREENS! Even when you figure out how to teleport, there is still ZERO loading screens. I didn't like it at first, but I toughed it out until I was able to use magic, and what I found was a truly immersive experience. This game is long, but  just when you think it's almost impossible, you find exactly what you needed to get by. This is an intricate and well thought out RPG that deserves to be recognized. Some of the world you will see in Kings Field is absolutely insane, much like Dark Souls. If you haven't played Kings Field yet, then you are seriously missing out.

column13: This game is pretty cool, it's got easy controls and in the ...
column14: This game is pretty cool, it's got easy controls and in the beginning when you hit new game it starts just like Shrek forever after does with Rumpelstiltskin telling the story and ripping pages out of the book. My 8 year old got the hang of it pretty quick after looking at the page in the game instructions with the controls on it. The controls are easy to remember once you start playing.  My 8 year old enjoys playing it on our compute, he is definitely better at the game then I am! You have Shrek, puss in boots, Donkey, and Fiona are in an alternate version of their lives where Shrek was never born.  Shrek signed a contract giving Rumpelstiltskin one day from his childhood without thinking so he could have one day of being "a real ogor" again, little did he know Rumpel would take the day he was born. Now in the game you get to be Shrek, Fiona, Donkey, and Puss in boots and complete quests to defeat Rumpel and get Shrek's life back! I am completely satisfied with this game and how easy it is for my kid to play.  The graphics are pretty good too. These are absolutely my very own honest opinion after having received and tried this product for free in exchange for an unbiased and honest review.
